value.name: The Flight Attendant
value.overview: Flight attendant Cassandra Bowden wakes in her hotel room hungover from the night before in Dubai with a dead body lying next to her. Afraid to call the police, she continues her morning as if nothing happened. In New York, she is met by FBI agents who question her about her recent layover in Bangkok. Still unable to piece the night together, she begins to wonder if she could be the killer.

value.name: The Flight Attendants
value.overview: A humorous series authored by Saša Al Hamad, which follows the adventures of rebellious stewards and pilots of an imaginary airline.

value.name: The Flight Attendant Murders
value.overview: A re-examination of the brutal murders of four flight attendants in the 70s and 80s. Is the wrong man behind bars? If so - will the victims' families ever get justice? Part of True Crime on Channel 4.
